Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2%unit}, separating whites from greens. Trim and
finely dice half the @Cucumber{1%unit} (all for 4 servings).

In a #medium bowl{}, combine scallion greens, diced cucumber,
@Rice Wine Vinegar{5%teaspoon}, 1⁄2 tsp sugar, and 1⁄4 tsp @salt{}. Set aside,
stirring occasionally.

Open package of @Chopped Chicken Breast{10%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
chicken and scallion whites; season with salt and @Pepper{}. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until beginning to brown, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @Shredded Red Cabbage{4%ounce}, @Hoisin Sauce{2%tablespoon},
@Sweet Thai Chili Sauce{1%ounce}, and 1⁄4 cup water (1/3 cup for 4 servings).
Cook, stirring occasionally, until sauce has thickened and chicken is cooked
through, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Wrap @Flour Tortillas{6%unit} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and
pliable, about ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between #plates{}; fill with hoisin chicken and as much cucumber
relish (draining first) as you like. Garnish with @Sesame Seeds{1%tablespoon}
and serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.